cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is primarily focused on object detection in videos, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed approach involves using adaptive patch-of-interest composition to balance detection accuracy and speed, which could also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the approach could be applied to multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories, as object detection is a crucial task in both fields.
